Freshly-laid eggs of Painted Turtles (Chrysemys picta) obtained from Iowa turtle farms were incubated in moistened-sand14 following standard protocols49. Programmable incubators were set to replicate (a) hourly thermal profiles recorded from natural nests in the field using Dallas Semiconductor iButton™ dataloggers with 0.5 °C precision (Fig. 2a,b), or (b) thermal profiles modified by an affine mathematical transformation that increases the variance of the profile (by ±2 °C, ±4 °C, ±6 °C) while preserving its general shape (Fig. 2b–d). Thermal profiles were affine-transformed using the equation1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
